  '<h2 id="bounce">Bounce intake <a class="anchor" href="#bounce">#</a></h2>',
  '<p><code>b.mailBounce.handler(opts)</code> returns Express-style middleware that accepts inbound webhook callbacks from Postmark, SES, Resend, or a custom parser, normalizes their wildly different event shapes into one internal <code>BounceEvent</code>, runs an operator-supplied <code>verify</code> check, emits <code>system.mail.bounce</code> on the audit chain, and calls the operator <code>onBounce</code> callback. Suppression-tracking is the operator\'s data store — the framework normalizes the event but does NOT itself maintain a suppression table.</p>',
  '<h3>b.mailBounce.handler(opts)</h3>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">{',
  '  vendor:    "postmark" | "ses" | "resend" | "custom",',
