  '<h2 id="dkim-verify">b.mail.dkim.verify(rfc822, opts) <a class="anchor" href="#dkim-verify">#</a></h2>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">{',
  '  dnsLookup:  async (qname, type) => txtRecords,   // optional; defaults to node:dns/promises.resolveTxt',
  '  audit:      auditInstance,                        // default: false',
  '}</code></pre>',
  '<p>RFC 6376 DKIM-Signature verifier — counterpart to <code>b.mail.dkim.create</code>. Walks every <code>DKIM-Signature</code> header in the message, fetches the signing public key from DNS TXT at <code>&lt;selector&gt;._domainkey.&lt;domain&gt;</code>, canonicalizes the body + headers per the signature\'s <code>c=</code> tag, and verifies the cryptographic signature. Returns one result per signature: <code>{ d, s, alg, result, errors }</code> where <code>result</code> is <code>pass</code> / <code>fail</code> / <code>permerror</code> / <code>temperror</code> / <code>none</code>. Supports rsa-sha256 and ed25519-sha256.</p>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">// A message with no DKIM-Signature header returns a single "none" result.',
